		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Char creation tip #1:<br>Do not play a halfling.<br><br>Just kidding! I would put say 3/4 in Wis, and<br>1/4 in Sta. (For more of a caster role).<br><br>Dvordigan<br>Wood Elf Druid of the 9th Season<br>Mithaniel Marr&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td>

		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Dec 14th 8:35 PM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=9768055479607&num=6&page=0&post=1&replyto=97682610711319"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=97682610711319></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=7137"><span id=>LiselleSilverwolf</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />10 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=LiselleSilverwolf&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I would agree entirely with your intention to max Wisdom. For druids, higher wisdom equals more mana and mana is life - not just for us, but also for the people we group with. I had a scary moment in Oasis once, where the difference between victory and the Now Loading message was the one point of damage inflicted by my damage shield, the only spell I had enough mana to cast...but that's a story for another time.<br><br>As to where to put your extra points, I will relate the decisions I made when creating my druid based on what I knew at the time. There are obviously other ways of doing this and I am sure that others will have different opinions. <br><br>Firstly, I ruled out Intelligence and Charisma as five points was not enough to make a significant difference to these stats and cancel out the penalty for being under 75. This left Strength, Stamina, Agility and Dexterity. <br><br>Strength determines how much you can carry and also supposedly influences the amount of damage you do in melee combat. I chose not to increase this stat at creation, primarily because many of the standard druid items, e.g. Foreman's Tunic and Silver Ruby Veil give Str bonuses. In addition, druids get a Str buff and halflings can obtain the Leatherfoot Raider Skullcap via a quest. This also gives a Str bonus. I can achieve a Str of 100 with my buff and cap on and this gives plenty of carrying capacity.<br><br>Stamina affects the amount of hit points you have and also seems to determine how long you can hold your breath underwater, how long you can use two-handed weapons, etc. I did not raise Sta at creation as I felt that the five points would not make an appreciable difference to my hit points. Also, I conciously decided to concentrate solely on one-handed weapons, so Sta is not such an issue for me. Add to this the fact that we get the spell Enduring Breath to allow us to stay underwater for a long time, and Sta did not seem to be a priority for me. <br><br>Dexterity seems to affect how quickly you learn weapon skills and also how often a weapon will do it's special effect, or proc. As above, I was only aiming to balance two weapon skills (1HS, and 1HB) so did not feel this was too important. Also, at the time, I was not aware of many druid weapons with a proc, so did not boost Dex at creation. Incidentally, I would advise you to practice all three weapon skills if at all possible. Flexibility is the key to our success and you cannot guarantee that one or two weapons will suit all occasions.<br><br>So, all of this has been a rather long-winded way of saying that I put my extra five points into Agility. Agi seems to influence Armour Class as well as how quickly you learn certain defensive skills. Bitter experience with other characters had taught me that it was difficult to cast spells with mobs beating down on me, so anything that improved my chances of not getting hit sounded like a good idea. Most of our armour is leather-class and is light, both in terms of AC and weight (another reason why I didn't boost Str at creation) so we need to avoid getting hit if at all possible. I figured that decent Agi would help improve the Dodge skill which we get at level 15, which would therefore improve my chances of getting spells off if things turned nasty.<br><br>So, congratulations on your choice of race and class. I hope your druid brings you many hours of enjoyment and your experiences prompt you to explore the many other options that EverQuest offers. <br><br>Finally, whilst the Druid is an excellent solo class for many reasons, the EQ experience is improved by good groups. And never forget that a little help often goes a long way. I have lost count of the number of times a heal or SoW has been rewarded by a grateful player, and damage shielding tanks in Crushbone worked wonders for my faction :)<br><br><br>P.S. I have to say that I am impressed with your decisiveness...it took me many, many characters until I found the ones that suited my playing style.<br><br>P.P.S Liselle, my Druid, is now level 27<br></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Happy hunting...<br><br>Ellaria - Ranger<br>Liselle - Druid<br>Melisande - ShadowKnight<br></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
